WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:52.469
ALL FIGURES, INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:52.552 --> 00:54.971
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED
SAFELY IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES

00:55.055 --> 00:57.974
SEOUL HIGH PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:59.726 --> 01:01.978
How are you acquainted
with Mr. Jeon Sang-ho?

01:04.439 --> 01:06.775
He was my client.

01:07.358 --> 01:08.443
You were his attorney?

01:09.527 --> 01:11.279
What were you defending him for?

01:11.362 --> 01:12.489
That…

01:14.741 --> 01:18.745
I cannot disclose it
due to my duty of confidentiality.

01:22.999 --> 01:25.919
Then, when were you first
acquainted with him?

01:26.753 --> 01:28.922
Not long ago.

01:30.006 --> 01:34.385
Are you saying
it was just before his death?

01:35.345 --> 01:36.346
Kind of.

01:40.517 --> 01:43.728
Mr. Shin, are you playing games with me?

01:47.106 --> 01:48.650
My son-in-law's attorney?

01:49.651 --> 01:52.654
It seems Mr. Jeon retained him
before he passed away.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.824
That's totally new to me.

01:55.907 --> 01:59.994
I saw traces of him
at the attorney's office.

02:00.078 --> 02:03.164
I compared it with his handwriting
at the lab, and it looked the same.

02:03.248 --> 02:07.669
He had a habit of writing on the wall
or anywhere to prove what questioned him.

02:09.170 --> 02:10.171
Now, tell me.

02:10.672 --> 02:12.924
Why did my son-in-law's attorney
come here?

02:13.007 --> 02:14.175
Why did he go on a rampage?

02:14.759 --> 02:16.469
Oh, that.

02:17.637 --> 02:19.305
I think he's got a mental issue.

02:20.306 --> 02:23.518
He sees and hears things.

02:25.603 --> 02:27.021
If you'd like to sue him, I can…

02:27.814 --> 02:29.107
No.

02:29.190 --> 02:31.317
Su-jeong's second instance
is enough of a headache.

02:31.901 --> 02:33.153
Let's not add more to it.

02:35.697 --> 02:36.698
Of course.

02:55.091 --> 02:56.593
It's late. Let's call it here.

02:56.676 --> 02:58.845
Why didn't you tell me
that Mr. Jeon's research was

02:58.928 --> 03:02.891
about developing a cure
for your wife's Concello disease?

03:02.974 --> 03:04.017
That…

03:04.726 --> 03:07.061
has nothing to do with this case.

03:07.145 --> 03:08.605
According to people around you,

03:09.647 --> 03:12.775
Mr. Jeon wanted to drop the research.

03:13.401 --> 03:14.402
Is this true?

03:14.485 --> 03:15.612
Who said such a thing?

03:17.363 --> 03:21.075
If it's true, it may be seen
as a powerful motive for murder.

03:29.792 --> 03:31.836
It's already been 17 years now.

03:34.005 --> 03:37.091
-Honey, the soup is ready.
-Okay.

03:48.019 --> 03:51.814
The Korean section was a bit hard,
but I could handle everything else.

03:53.650 --> 03:55.026
Why don't you take private lessons?

03:55.109 --> 03:56.444
I don't want to.

03:57.862 --> 03:58.863
Or…

04:01.115 --> 04:02.116
why don't I help you?

04:03.117 --> 04:04.118
That's worse.

04:08.289 --> 04:10.250
Honey, are you okay?

04:12.794 --> 04:14.379
I'm okay.

04:14.462 --> 04:16.130
Maybe it's because I couldn't sleep much.

04:16.214 --> 04:17.840
Shouldn't you go see a doctor?

04:18.424 --> 04:20.468
It's already the third time this week.

04:29.644 --> 04:31.521
The MRI scan result says…

04:31.604 --> 04:33.273
That was the beginning.

04:37.110 --> 04:39.862
Her disease destroyed our family.

04:39.946 --> 04:40.947
Honey.

04:42.949 --> 04:43.950
Mom.

04:48.454 --> 04:52.917
From then on, I took her to the
best doctors to find an optimal solution,

04:53.001 --> 04:54.419
but nothing worked.

04:57.171 --> 04:59.299
Still, I couldn't give up.

05:02.010 --> 05:05.847
Since I was a scientist,
I decided to resolve it myself.

05:07.807 --> 05:10.268
I wanted to save my wife
with my own ability.

05:43.676 --> 05:45.344
When did you come, Dad?

05:45.428 --> 05:46.679
Su-jeong.

05:48.181 --> 05:49.432
God doesn't exist.

05:51.392 --> 05:52.935
What can save your mom

05:53.936 --> 05:55.146
is only science.

06:18.628 --> 06:21.214
Repeated failures made me anxious.

06:26.302 --> 06:27.678
And I realized

06:28.429 --> 06:30.807
that I needed someone better than me.

06:32.266 --> 06:34.894
That was Mr. Jeon Sang-ho, wasn't it?

06:37.772 --> 06:41.400
But he called a halt to the research.

06:42.401 --> 06:45.696
You must've hated him enough to kill him,
Mr. Kim Tae-jun.

07:13.558 --> 07:17.854
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

07:23.401 --> 07:24.402
Prosecutor Kim.

07:24.485 --> 07:25.695
Yes?

07:25.778 --> 07:27.780
The forensic analysis result is out.

07:28.906 --> 07:31.826
Shin I-rang's fingerprints
were found inside the gloves.

07:31.909 --> 07:35.288
It's way off Jeon Sang-ho's estimated time
of death too.

07:36.164 --> 07:39.417
They assume the fingerprints were
from when he dug up the body.

07:39.500 --> 07:44.088
Does this mean Shin I-rang is
only the first discoverer of the body?

07:45.173 --> 07:46.466
As it stands now, yes.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.304
He went up the mountain
and found the body by himself?

07:52.638 --> 07:54.056
Who made the report?

07:54.140 --> 07:56.476
It was through an emergency call,

07:56.559 --> 07:58.186
but who reported it is unknown.

08:08.613 --> 08:09.614
Jeon Sang-ho?

08:10.823 --> 08:11.949
How did he do it?

08:16.037 --> 08:17.538
There has to be something.

08:27.131 --> 08:29.091
I collected and checked
all footage within a kilometer.

08:29.175 --> 08:31.302
Fortunately, you weren't captured.

08:32.220 --> 08:33.721
Still, I terminated it all.

08:34.805 --> 08:35.806
Good job.

08:38.309 --> 08:39.310
Oh, right.

08:40.311 --> 08:41.646
Tail Shin I-rang for some time.

08:42.230 --> 08:43.231
Yes, sir.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.911
You'll be asked to come in again soon.

08:57.537 --> 09:00.248
Keep your phone on
and be ready to take the call anytime.

09:00.831 --> 09:02.166
Okay.

09:08.422 --> 09:10.925
-I-rang.
-I-rang. Are you okay?

09:14.428 --> 09:15.429
Mom?

09:16.889 --> 09:19.892
You're supposed to have pure white tofu
for a good change,

09:19.976 --> 09:20.977
but the store isn't open yet.

09:21.060 --> 09:22.311
TODAY SOY MILK
ORIGINAL

09:23.104 --> 09:24.855
I was feeling hungry anyway.

09:25.523 --> 09:26.524
Thanks, Bong-su.

09:27.233 --> 09:29.485
I bought all kinds, so drink all you want.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.445
This one is warm.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.867
Anyway, did you stay up all night
in the car?

09:38.035 --> 09:40.663
Why did you? You should've waited at home.

09:40.746 --> 09:42.707
I couldn't do it
when my son was somewhere cold.

09:43.374 --> 09:46.544
Bong-su, I have a place to go with I-rang.

09:46.627 --> 09:48.129
Go back with the Father.

09:48.212 --> 09:49.338
Okay.

09:49.422 --> 09:52.425
Are we going somewhere? Where?

09:52.508 --> 09:53.801
You'll know when we get there.

10:06.147 --> 10:07.148
-Have some.
-I'm good.

10:07.231 --> 10:09.108
-It's all right.
-No, thank you.

10:14.405 --> 10:16.115
What is this about?

10:16.198 --> 10:18.618
You're scaring me.

10:21.078 --> 10:22.121
Mom.

10:24.498 --> 10:26.167
I knew it from the start.

10:26.751 --> 10:28.836
It didn't seem bad,

10:28.919 --> 10:32.506
so I asked the priest and Bong-su
to assist you.

10:33.257 --> 10:34.842
But this isn't right.

10:34.925 --> 10:37.595
What's wrong with you, Mom? Stop it.

10:37.678 --> 10:39.722
I should've done this in the beginning.

10:40.514 --> 10:43.309
I should've burned them all
when I discovered it.

10:43.392 --> 10:46.937
Mom, this is my office. This is my work.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.564
What if something bad happens to you?

10:49.565 --> 10:51.734
What if you get hurt?

10:53.778 --> 10:56.238
That's not going to happen.
I won't get hurt.

10:58.949 --> 11:00.409
What if you harm someone?

11:00.493 --> 11:01.494
I won't.

11:02.119 --> 11:03.496
I swear it won't happen again.

11:03.579 --> 11:05.247
How can you be sure of that?

11:05.331 --> 11:06.499
Because it's all…

11:09.126 --> 11:10.419
my fault.

11:11.879 --> 11:13.130
What?

11:14.882 --> 11:18.511
I lied to Sang-ho about the trial.

11:19.470 --> 11:22.056
In case he went out of control
and things got complicated,

11:23.099 --> 11:25.559
I hid the truth from him.

11:26.852 --> 11:28.938
Let alone getting murdered,

11:29.021 --> 11:32.108
he found out that the only person
listening to him was fooling him.

11:33.859 --> 11:35.903
I can only imagine how angry he was.

11:35.986 --> 11:37.822
That's not your fault.

11:38.781 --> 11:41.700
You weren't meant for this kind of work
in the first place.

11:41.784 --> 11:42.868
If not me…

11:44.161 --> 11:46.539
If not me,
who's going to listen to their stories?

11:48.416 --> 11:50.876
-I-rang.
-In the holding cell, I stopped to think…

11:53.129 --> 11:54.964
about why my life was turning this way,

11:56.215 --> 11:58.175
where it started to get messy,

11:58.259 --> 12:01.846
and what wrongs I committed
to deserve such difficult tasks.

12:01.929 --> 12:03.013
But then,

12:03.806 --> 12:07.560
I realized that the happiness I got
from both Gang-pung and Su-a

12:08.519 --> 12:11.522
was much bigger
than the difficulties I faced.

12:13.357 --> 12:15.484
Rather than money, fame,
or anything like that,

12:16.652 --> 12:19.155
I realized how precious it was
to help souls

12:19.989 --> 12:22.241
and how lucky I was

12:22.324 --> 12:26.203
to be able to help them.

12:35.504 --> 12:36.547
So,

12:38.257 --> 12:40.134
you'll continue?

12:43.095 --> 12:44.096
Yes.

12:45.639 --> 12:46.640
I want to.

12:48.058 --> 12:49.059
I'll do it.

12:57.026 --> 12:58.611
Just who do you take after?

13:01.363 --> 13:03.365
What if something like yesterday
happens again?

13:03.866 --> 13:04.867
Then,

13:05.868 --> 13:07.495
I'll do as you say.

13:07.578 --> 13:10.372
Are you sure?
Can you really put an end to this?

13:10.456 --> 13:11.457
Yes.

13:12.333 --> 13:15.252
I'll burn these all myself.

13:21.509 --> 13:22.510
Be careful, okay?

13:23.719 --> 13:28.557
You must never get yourself hurt
or hurt others. Got it?

13:29.183 --> 13:30.184
Okay.

13:31.519 --> 13:33.521
I'll be very, very careful.

13:35.105 --> 13:36.357
I promise.

14:03.592 --> 14:04.802
Don't worry.

14:06.929 --> 14:08.264
I'm not like Dad.

14:18.023 --> 14:19.817
Thank you, Mr. Attorney.

14:22.570 --> 14:23.821
Don't say that.

14:24.780 --> 14:26.282
I'm the one who's sorry

14:27.032 --> 14:28.325
and also grateful.

14:30.953 --> 14:32.204
Anyway,

14:33.122 --> 14:35.249
did you think
the culprit was your father-in-law?

14:35.833 --> 14:37.877
Is that why you went to him?

14:37.960 --> 14:40.421
What led you to such an idea?

14:43.924 --> 14:45.885
Is it hard to tell me?

14:45.968 --> 14:48.512
I'm not trying to hide it,

14:49.763 --> 14:50.890
but I want to check it

14:52.141 --> 14:53.601
with Su-jeong first.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.437
And when I become sure,

14:57.021 --> 14:58.522
I'll tell you everything.

15:00.649 --> 15:03.903
You want to meet her?
She's locked up in the detention center.

15:06.363 --> 15:07.948
I don't think it's a good idea.

15:09.074 --> 15:12.912
If you see her,
you'll lose your calm for sure.

15:12.995 --> 15:15.789
Then yesterday's ruckus may repeat.

15:16.707 --> 15:17.958
Right.

15:18.751 --> 15:21.170
I'll ask her on your behalf.

15:22.046 --> 15:23.881
Tell me all that you want to ask her.

15:24.465 --> 15:26.592
What about me?

15:27.760 --> 15:31.805
Of course, you'll wait outside
so that you won't possess me.

15:31.889 --> 15:33.891
Somewhere as far as you can be.

15:33.974 --> 15:35.100
Right.

15:35.684 --> 15:36.685
Far away.

15:37.895 --> 15:38.896
Right.

15:40.481 --> 15:41.649
Hello.

15:45.903 --> 15:46.946
Prosecutor Kim.

15:51.367 --> 15:52.868
I have a favor to ask of you.

15:52.952 --> 15:53.953
Answer me first.

15:54.620 --> 15:57.623
I heard you took Attorney Shin's family
to Mr. Kim's house.

15:57.706 --> 15:58.874
What happened?

15:58.958 --> 16:01.251
I honestly can't explain it.

16:02.169 --> 16:03.420
Maybe I got swept up in the moment.

16:03.504 --> 16:06.423
You aren't one to get swept up
in the moment, are you?

16:08.008 --> 16:11.136
Is the interrogation date scheduled
for Ms. Kim Su-jeong?

16:12.137 --> 16:13.472
There won't be an interrogation.

16:13.555 --> 16:15.391
She refused to do it.

16:16.016 --> 16:18.102
The walls are closing in on her.

16:18.185 --> 16:19.853
I wonder what's gotten into her.

16:20.646 --> 16:21.647
Beats me.

16:23.023 --> 16:26.026
I need the list of suspects,
the case materials,

16:26.110 --> 16:28.654
and Mr. Jeon's autopsy report.

16:28.737 --> 16:32.199
I'm making an official request
as Ms. Kim's attorney.

16:38.831 --> 16:39.832
Hello?

16:39.915 --> 16:42.376
Attorney Shin just entered
the Seoul Detention Center.

16:42.459 --> 16:43.794
Why?

16:43.877 --> 16:46.588
Jeon Sang-ho's wife, Kim Su-jeong,
is locked up here.

16:49.174 --> 16:50.968
Do you know any guards there?

17:15.451 --> 17:18.120
I hope you're doing well. Yes.

17:18.954 --> 17:20.581
Don't worry.

17:20.664 --> 17:22.833
Recording is a piece of cake.

17:28.464 --> 17:29.465
What was that?

17:35.387 --> 17:37.306
Inmate 1023, Kim Su-jeong.

17:41.310 --> 17:42.394
Where did my pen go?

17:44.063 --> 17:46.023
Gosh, maybe I forgot to bring it.

17:46.690 --> 17:47.733
Mr. Attorney.

17:47.816 --> 17:49.735
What are you doing here? Go away.

17:50.527 --> 17:52.112
Do we have a problem?

17:53.989 --> 17:56.867
No, not at all.

17:56.950 --> 17:59.453
-This man--
-Leave it up to me and just go.

18:00.996 --> 18:02.164
I must stay here.

18:02.247 --> 18:05.626
It's our rule to have a general visitation
accompanied by a guard.

18:05.709 --> 18:08.962
Oh, this isn't a general visitation.

18:09.588 --> 18:10.589
I'm an attorney.

18:11.340 --> 18:12.466
I see.

18:12.549 --> 18:15.928
I wrote it on the visitation request too.

18:16.011 --> 18:19.932
Oh, I guess I missed that part.

18:21.850 --> 18:24.144
Will you leave me alone now?

18:25.604 --> 18:26.855
Sure.

18:26.939 --> 18:28.065
Wait.

18:30.901 --> 18:32.736
That…

18:34.905 --> 18:37.825
W-What about it?

18:39.034 --> 18:40.452
Could I borrow it?

18:41.036 --> 18:43.288
I'll make sure to give it back to you
when I leave.

18:44.414 --> 18:45.874
Yes, thank--

18:45.958 --> 18:47.417
I mean…

18:47.501 --> 18:50.671
Please make sure you return it to me.

18:50.754 --> 18:52.840
Yes, of course.

18:52.923 --> 18:54.049
Okay.

19:07.062 --> 19:08.063
Oh, no.

19:14.528 --> 19:15.529
I heard…

19:19.950 --> 19:23.078
you found my husband's body.

19:24.746 --> 19:26.498
Was it really him?

19:29.334 --> 19:31.295
Was it really my husband, Sang-ho?

19:33.005 --> 19:34.006
Yes.

19:35.090 --> 19:38.552
Unfortunately, it was Mr. Jeon Sang-ho.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.638
It really was him…

19:47.769 --> 19:48.770
Mr. Attorney.

19:59.239 --> 20:01.283
He did nothing wrong.

20:02.659 --> 20:06.413
If he hadn't married me, he would've
lived happily as a successful scientist.

20:07.789 --> 20:11.043
He died because he was unlucky enough
to marry someone like me.

20:15.172 --> 20:17.674
I feel so sorry for him.

20:34.358 --> 20:35.609
Attorney Shin?

20:36.985 --> 20:38.320
Why are you crying?

20:49.539 --> 20:50.540
Su-jeong.

20:52.834 --> 20:53.835
Excuse me?

20:56.255 --> 20:57.381
It's me, Sang-ho.

21:00.926 --> 21:02.135
Your husband,

21:03.387 --> 21:04.429
Jeon Sang-ho.

21:07.557 --> 21:08.809
What are you saying?

21:09.935 --> 21:11.019
Are you out of your mind?

21:12.354 --> 21:14.231
Excuse me.

21:14.815 --> 21:16.316
-Guard.
-I'm peckish.

21:18.694 --> 21:20.112
I'm peckish.

21:21.363 --> 21:24.866
I'm suddenly feeling so peckish.

21:31.331 --> 21:32.332
I'm peckish too.

21:35.252 --> 21:38.588
Everyone seems hungry.
Should we eat something?

21:38.672 --> 21:40.132
Sounds good.

21:40.215 --> 21:41.258
What should we have?

21:41.341 --> 21:43.468
Because it wasn't easy for me
to say "I love you,"

21:44.428 --> 21:46.513
instead of using "love"

21:46.596 --> 21:49.891
"peckish" became our secret signal.

22:07.909 --> 22:09.494
Is it really you, Sang-ho?

22:09.578 --> 22:10.787
Our first kiss was

22:11.747 --> 22:13.749
on September 4, 2018

22:14.875 --> 22:16.126
in the closet of my house.

22:17.544 --> 22:19.296
We were excited to pick January 2,

22:19.379 --> 22:21.590
Isaac Asimov's birthday,
for our wedding date.

22:31.391 --> 22:34.978
I looked so much for you.

22:35.062 --> 22:36.313
Why?

22:36.897 --> 22:39.941
Did you think I hid the cure
before I died?

22:40.025 --> 22:41.568
That's not it.

22:43.445 --> 22:44.446
Right.

22:45.072 --> 22:46.073
Honestly,

22:47.407 --> 22:49.701
I was attracted
to how much you loved your family.

22:50.410 --> 22:52.162
I admit it.

22:54.164 --> 22:57.584
You sacrificed your everything
for your beloved family.

22:58.627 --> 23:00.045
I felt like I'd become happy

23:01.129 --> 23:03.215
if I married someone like you.

23:04.633 --> 23:05.634
But

23:06.635 --> 23:08.762
I couldn't be part of your family
in the end.

23:08.845 --> 23:10.514
Why aren't we getting any good news yet?

23:11.056 --> 23:13.058
What if it ends up falling through?

23:13.141 --> 23:15.227
Wait patiently, Dad.

23:15.310 --> 23:16.812
Let's count on Sang-ho.

23:16.895 --> 23:18.980
I've waited all this time!

23:19.689 --> 23:22.400
I'm only saying it
because there has been no progress!

23:25.654 --> 23:27.155
To your family,

23:28.115 --> 23:29.991
I was just a stranger you chose

23:31.284 --> 23:32.702
out of necessity.

23:34.287 --> 23:35.455
No.

23:37.165 --> 23:38.625
I didn't come to you

23:39.459 --> 23:40.919
just because of the cure.

23:45.132 --> 23:46.466
Just if,

23:48.176 --> 23:50.095
like the police said…

23:53.348 --> 23:55.809
you were dead for real…

23:59.396 --> 24:02.482
I wanted to let you know how I felt
by any means possible.

24:02.566 --> 24:03.567
Stop lying.

24:06.111 --> 24:07.279
Your father killed me.

24:08.989 --> 24:10.365
You even confessed.

24:11.366 --> 24:12.450
Don't lie.

24:16.246 --> 24:19.291
My dad killed you?
What are you talking about?

24:21.126 --> 24:24.504
When I confessed,
it wasn't because he killed you.

24:24.588 --> 24:25.714
Then…

24:28.258 --> 24:29.759
why did you turn yourself in?

24:30.719 --> 24:32.304
No one is there to prove…

24:34.723 --> 24:38.101
that Dad was home
when the murder took place.

24:39.561 --> 24:42.147
If he gets arrested…

24:43.440 --> 24:45.066
You know it well enough.

24:46.234 --> 24:48.862
Mom needs Dad at every second.

24:48.945 --> 24:50.614
You confessed to what you didn't do

24:51.740 --> 24:53.283
for that ridiculous reason?

24:54.284 --> 24:55.535
What about U-ju?

24:56.286 --> 24:57.537
Without you, U-ju…

24:58.872 --> 25:00.248
U-ju needs you!

25:01.082 --> 25:02.250
U-ju…

25:04.836 --> 25:07.005
can survive without me.

25:10.008 --> 25:11.676
Mom will die without Dad.

25:17.474 --> 25:19.226
I had no choice.

25:23.396 --> 25:24.981
I'm sorry, Sang-ho.

25:45.085 --> 25:46.962
Geez, my eyes are red.

25:48.380 --> 25:49.506
I'm sorry.

25:50.298 --> 25:52.634
You shouldn't have come.

25:52.717 --> 25:53.927
I told you not to.

25:54.010 --> 25:55.720
I didn't mean to.

25:57.097 --> 25:58.098
Pen.

25:59.057 --> 26:00.809
The pen.

26:00.892 --> 26:02.269
Oh, right.

26:02.352 --> 26:04.396
I forgot to give it back to him.

26:04.479 --> 26:06.106
It's not just a pen.

26:06.189 --> 26:07.607
It's a recorder.

26:07.691 --> 26:09.025
What?

26:14.906 --> 26:17.534
Gosh, I'm lost for words.

26:18.159 --> 26:19.869
What is it? Did something happen?

26:19.953 --> 26:21.329
Where is the voice recorder?

26:21.413 --> 26:22.831
Look.

26:22.914 --> 26:26.418
That Shin I-rang or whoever is a lunatic.

26:35.176 --> 26:37.721
Excuse me. You still have my pen.

26:37.804 --> 26:39.014
Don't touch me.

26:39.097 --> 26:41.725
I said, give me my pen back.

26:43.977 --> 26:46.479
I may be a bookworm,
but don't underestimate me.

26:48.064 --> 26:49.899
Even a worm will turn.

26:50.525 --> 26:52.360
And a cornered rat will fight back.

26:53.945 --> 26:54.946
Get it?

26:59.326 --> 27:01.369
Someone's watching me?

27:01.453 --> 27:04.039
Yes, 100%.
There are no other possibilities.

27:05.248 --> 27:07.584
Let's figure that out later.

27:08.793 --> 27:10.295
What did Ms. Kim say?

27:10.879 --> 27:12.380
Is her father the accomplice?

27:13.131 --> 27:14.424
No.

27:15.175 --> 27:16.843
Then, who is the culprit?

27:16.926 --> 27:17.969
Su-jeong.

27:18.928 --> 27:21.139
Until the actual culprit gets caught,

27:21.222 --> 27:24.184
people need to think she's the murderer.

27:27.896 --> 27:29.481
He quit developing a cure?

27:30.523 --> 27:33.276
In case it was considered
a motive for murder,

27:33.360 --> 27:37.447
Kim Tae-jun kept his wife's disease
and Jeon Sang-ho's research a secret.

27:39.699 --> 27:43.620
So that motive for murder applies
to both Kim Su-jeong and Kim Tae-jun.

27:44.746 --> 27:46.414
Which one are you suspecting?

27:46.498 --> 27:50.418
For now, I have a third person in mind.

27:51.044 --> 27:52.045
There's another suspect?

27:52.879 --> 27:55.340
Yes, but I'll have to look into it.

27:58.009 --> 28:00.303
You're not a detective, Attorney Han.

28:01.221 --> 28:03.515
Kim Su-jeong declined legal presentation.

28:04.265 --> 28:06.434
Pulling out is important
when there's good reason.

28:06.518 --> 28:11.606
Kim Su-jeong will be found not guilty
if the actual culprit can be proved.

28:11.689 --> 28:12.982
So what's your plan?

28:13.066 --> 28:15.360
I'll meet someone who can prove it.

28:16.986 --> 28:18.321
U-ju…

28:19.322 --> 28:21.699
can survive without me.

28:23.535 --> 28:25.912
Mom will die without Dad.

28:27.539 --> 28:28.957
That's the end.

28:29.541 --> 28:32.710
So, you tried to develop a cure
for your mother-in-law.

28:34.379 --> 28:37.966
The three of you wanted to protect
the ones you loved.

28:38.800 --> 28:40.427
I fully understand how you felt.

28:50.770 --> 28:52.230
Where are you going?

28:52.814 --> 28:54.149
To a restaurant, to eat.

28:54.899 --> 28:55.942
What?

28:57.610 --> 29:00.864
I'll stuff myself, regain energy,
and find the real culprit.

29:02.240 --> 29:04.951
But if that's Kim Tae-jun,

29:05.618 --> 29:07.120
I'll put him behind bars.

29:07.787 --> 29:11.332
That's my duty as your attorney.

29:18.465 --> 29:19.549
Shin I-rang?

29:19.632 --> 29:24.387
From the start, he knew
exactly where the murder took place.

29:24.471 --> 29:28.975
Kim Su-jeong murdered her husband
brutally in the bathroom.

29:30.185 --> 29:33.188
Her denial is a lie.

29:33.271 --> 29:35.440
He also knew
where Jeon Sang-ho's body was.

29:36.858 --> 29:39.027
He probably knows more.

29:39.986 --> 29:40.987
So?

29:41.571 --> 29:44.324
I'm going to make use of him.

30:01.174 --> 30:03.259
I can also pull tricks.

30:19.567 --> 30:20.777
Apologize?

30:20.860 --> 30:24.239
I lost my temper in your office that day.

30:25.532 --> 30:28.451
I misunderstood you
without bothering to hear you out.

30:29.160 --> 30:30.703
I was harsh on you too.

30:36.000 --> 30:37.001
I'm sorry.

30:38.127 --> 30:40.922
Do you believe me, then?

30:43.091 --> 30:44.884
And that Sang-ho's spirit is here?

30:46.594 --> 30:48.263
I believe you.

30:49.472 --> 30:50.723
Isn't that what matters?

30:53.560 --> 30:54.602
What a relief.

30:55.270 --> 30:58.982
Actually, your last remark
was quite hurtful.

30:59.899 --> 31:02.485
You said I used other people's suffering.

31:02.569 --> 31:03.736
That's…

31:07.574 --> 31:08.658
I see.

31:09.826 --> 31:13.454
It's okay now that I know how you feel.

31:14.330 --> 31:18.793
Why don't we go to my office
instead of talking here?

31:19.419 --> 31:21.588
I'll officially introduce
you and Sang-ho to each other.

31:23.089 --> 31:26.050
OKCHEON BUILDING

31:27.886 --> 31:29.137
I hate this.

31:33.766 --> 31:37.353
This is Attorney Han Na-hyun.
She's Ms. Kim Su-jeong's attorney.

31:39.022 --> 31:40.023
And this is

31:40.940 --> 31:43.359
Ms. Kim's husband, Jeon Sang-ho.

31:47.780 --> 31:49.157
Hello.

31:51.284 --> 31:52.493
Hello.

31:56.998 --> 31:58.499
Good.

31:58.583 --> 32:02.003
It's not as awkward as expected, is it?

32:14.849 --> 32:18.728
Do you have any questions for Sang-ho?

32:18.811 --> 32:21.648
I have a lot of questions

32:22.607 --> 32:23.900
about the case.

32:26.861 --> 32:29.113
There are a lot of lingering doubts,

32:29.822 --> 32:32.408
but Ms. Kim wouldn't tell me.

32:33.201 --> 32:34.410
Then, ask him.

32:35.078 --> 32:37.747
He'll tell you everything he knows.

32:38.748 --> 32:40.583
I want to know
if there was anything unusual

32:40.667 --> 32:42.752
on the night of the murder.

32:46.589 --> 32:47.840
After arguing with my wife,

32:48.925 --> 32:50.259
I went to my study.

32:50.843 --> 32:53.221
She went upstairs straightaway to sleep.

32:53.805 --> 32:55.932
He went to the study
after arguing with Su-jeong.

32:56.015 --> 32:58.601
And Su-jeong went straight to sleep.

32:59.602 --> 33:01.354
It's odd now that I think of it.

33:01.437 --> 33:03.606
Are you sure you didn't hear anything

33:03.690 --> 33:05.900
on the night your husband got murdered?

33:06.859 --> 33:07.860
No.

33:08.361 --> 33:10.321
I fell asleep as soon as I lied down.

33:12.615 --> 33:14.701
When I woke up, the sun was already up.

33:14.784 --> 33:17.620
She was mentally unstable

33:17.704 --> 33:20.415
and that day, she even had a bad fight
with her husband.

33:20.957 --> 33:24.794
How was she able
to sleep deeply enough to hear nothing?

33:24.877 --> 33:28.506
It was probably
because of her chamomile tea.

33:29.132 --> 33:31.926
After U-ju was born,
Su-jeong suffered from serious insomnia.

33:32.468 --> 33:35.972
But the chamomile tea from Hyo-jung
helped her sleep well.

33:36.973 --> 33:37.974
Chamomile?

33:39.308 --> 33:40.309
Chamomile?

33:41.269 --> 33:44.731
He says a man named Hyo-jung
got her chamomile tea.

33:45.314 --> 33:46.315
Hyo-jung?

33:47.191 --> 33:48.609
Is this about Gu Hyo-jung?

33:49.193 --> 33:51.154
Yes, that's right.

33:51.237 --> 33:53.990
How do you know him?

33:54.073 --> 33:56.242
I went to check Mr. Jeon's lab
and met him there.

33:57.577 --> 33:58.619
I see.

33:59.579 --> 34:03.750
I guess this man is quite the caring type.

34:03.833 --> 34:05.084
Or maybe

34:06.419 --> 34:08.504
he has a crush on Su-jeong.

34:10.173 --> 34:11.299
I doubt he still does.

34:11.924 --> 34:13.509
Then, he used to?

34:16.471 --> 34:19.098
Gu Hyo-jung used to
have a crush on Su-jeong.

34:23.394 --> 34:24.604
I discovered it by chance.

34:31.819 --> 34:33.988
He didn't make any moves
after our wedding,

34:34.572 --> 34:36.407
so I figured he moved on.

34:36.908 --> 34:39.827
Obsessive love is a motive
for quite a lot of murders.

34:41.037 --> 34:42.121
Not him.

34:42.205 --> 34:46.042
I hear the culprit is
taller than 180 cm and sturdy.

34:46.125 --> 34:48.878
But he's around 170 cm tall and slim.

34:49.837 --> 34:51.881
Gu Hyo-jung is short and--

34:51.964 --> 34:54.634
I know he's short and small.

34:55.760 --> 34:56.969
But he…

34:57.553 --> 34:58.596
Nice to meet you.

35:00.139 --> 35:01.224
Hello.

35:01.724 --> 35:04.519
He had a slim but toned physique.

35:05.645 --> 35:07.772
His palm was hard with calluses.

35:09.107 --> 35:11.984
Besides, he gave me
information that I never asked in detail.

35:12.068 --> 35:14.028
We even have a dorm for researchers.

35:14.570 --> 35:17.198
We can't go home often due to work.

35:17.907 --> 35:21.536
As if he were subtly making a way out.

35:21.619 --> 35:22.620
I see.

35:22.703 --> 35:27.792
Sang-ho had the best research outcomes,
and the Chief used him to save his wife.

35:28.334 --> 35:32.004
At the same time,
he led me to suspect Kim Tae-jun.

35:32.088 --> 35:33.464
What are you talking about?

35:33.548 --> 35:35.758
-I acted like I didn't follow…
-Ms. Kim took the blame for whom?

35:35.842 --> 35:37.218
…and he snapped at me.

35:37.301 --> 35:38.594
Isn't it obvious?

35:40.972 --> 35:42.140
The Chief.

35:42.723 --> 35:45.476
Obsessive love sure is
a major motive for murder,

35:46.102 --> 35:48.813
but it was only an old-time crush
in Gu Hyo-jung's case.

35:49.730 --> 35:52.733
Do you have other reasons
behind suspecting him?

36:03.119 --> 36:05.913
Gu Hyo-jung's research
was on animal cloning.

36:06.497 --> 36:08.291
Kim Tae-jun ceased that research.

36:08.374 --> 36:09.417
…A HALT TO UNETHICAL RESEARCH…

36:09.500 --> 36:11.210
Most of all, Gu Hyo-jung believes

36:11.294 --> 36:13.588
that Kim Tae-jun forced
his daughter to marry Sang-ho

36:13.671 --> 36:17.884
out of his blind desire
to develop a cure for his wife's disease.

36:19.218 --> 36:23.598
And what solidified
my suspicion of Gu Hyo-jung

36:25.016 --> 36:27.185
was the autopsy report on Mr. Jeon.

36:32.690 --> 36:33.941
POSTMORTEM PHENOMENA

36:34.525 --> 36:37.486
The culprit couldn't deliver
a fatal blow in one go.

36:38.821 --> 36:39.906
…REPEATED STRIKES…

36:39.989 --> 36:43.618
He hit the wrong spot several times.
I wondered why.

36:45.703 --> 36:47.246
Then, I remembered

36:47.955 --> 36:48.956
his glasses.

36:50.708 --> 36:53.127
Given the thickness and shape
of the lenses,

36:53.211 --> 36:54.879
he had to have serious farsightedness.

36:56.547 --> 36:59.091
The murder took place in the bathroom.

37:00.635 --> 37:04.680
Glasses fog up more easily
the older they are.

37:09.769 --> 37:11.520
With his farsightedness
and fogged-up glasses,

37:11.604 --> 37:13.898
he must've had to strike several times.

37:14.523 --> 37:17.026
The problem is
the estimated time of the murder.

37:17.860 --> 37:20.321
Gu Hyo-jung has a solid alibi.

37:22.365 --> 37:25.243
I checked all the researchers' alibis,

37:25.326 --> 37:28.412
and Gu Hyo-jung was
at the lab all day that day.

37:28.496 --> 37:30.373
He said he slept in the dorm.

37:30.998 --> 37:37.797
In fact, the CCTV camera by the entrance
captured him entering and not leaving.

37:40.258 --> 37:41.259
The lab

37:42.426 --> 37:45.137
has a passage without cameras.

37:56.732 --> 38:01.821
It was made to handle dead animals
under the radar of animal rights groups.

38:02.488 --> 38:04.907
No CCTV cameras are installed there.

38:06.450 --> 38:07.451
But…

38:10.830 --> 38:11.831
No.

38:12.498 --> 38:14.292
This assumption is too irrational.

38:14.375 --> 38:16.043
There's no reliable evidence whatsoever.

38:17.503 --> 38:20.172
Do you have the autopsy report with you?

38:21.799 --> 38:22.883
Why do you ask?

38:24.719 --> 38:26.554
I said he had a solid alibi.

38:26.637 --> 38:29.390
Sang-ho says there's an exit
without any CCTV cameras at the lab.

38:30.308 --> 38:34.061
And he saw something
the moment he was attacked.

38:37.940 --> 38:41.360
The medical examiner's opinion
on the murder weapon

38:41.444 --> 38:44.322
might help him recollect his memory.

38:47.408 --> 38:48.868
You said you believed me.

39:09.221 --> 39:14.143
"The murder weapon is assumed to be
a round metal stick

39:14.769 --> 39:17.855
that is 7.5 cm in diameter
with a hook-shaped end."

39:18.731 --> 39:23.444
A round metal stick that is 7.5 cm
in diameter with a hook-shaped end?

39:28.074 --> 39:29.283
Hey.

39:29.825 --> 39:31.160
You've gained weight.

39:32.370 --> 39:35.164
You must find it quite comfortable here.

39:35.247 --> 39:36.457
What are you doing?

39:37.958 --> 39:38.959
Oh, hey.

39:39.543 --> 39:41.170
I was playing with them.

39:41.253 --> 39:42.546
Don't do that.

39:43.672 --> 39:46.926
You may find it fun,
but the animals don't.

39:52.139 --> 39:53.933
Why did Hyo-jung…

39:55.393 --> 39:57.770
Hyo-jung is a senior researcher.

39:58.604 --> 39:59.688
That means

40:00.439 --> 40:02.441
he's likely to be the next chief.

40:02.525 --> 40:05.736
And a few days ago,

40:06.779 --> 40:08.114
Kim Tae-jun resigned.

40:20.167 --> 40:22.336
CERTIFICATE OF APPOINTMENT
GU HYO-JUNG

40:26.298 --> 40:28.134
From the sad incident…

40:28.217 --> 40:29.218
INAUGURATION CEREMONY

40:29.301 --> 40:32.471
…about our former researcher's death…

40:35.057 --> 40:38.352
to the sudden resignation
of Chief Kim Tae-jun,

40:38.436 --> 40:40.020
our lab is going through hard times.

40:45.151 --> 40:46.735
But at a time like this,

40:48.529 --> 40:50.364
I believe we must reflect on the past

40:50.865 --> 40:53.451
and make plans for the future.

40:54.368 --> 40:56.078
As your new Chief,

40:56.704 --> 41:00.124
I plan to resume
our animal cloning research,

41:00.207 --> 41:02.751
which was ceased by the former chief.

41:03.919 --> 41:04.962
Thank you.

41:13.929 --> 41:17.266
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

41:17.349 --> 41:18.434
Hello.

41:18.517 --> 41:21.937
We're here to deliver an extra meat order
to the staff cafeteria.

41:22.021 --> 41:23.147
Just a moment.

41:23.230 --> 41:24.482
They said it was urgent.

41:24.565 --> 41:27.193
If we're late, you might not get
to have your spicy pork.

41:27.276 --> 41:29.111
I know. It's people's favorite.

41:29.195 --> 41:31.197
-The spicy pork here is to die for.
-Right.

41:31.280 --> 41:33.115
The meat might go bad.

41:33.949 --> 41:36.660
-Great, it's open. Thanks.
-Thank you. Have a good day!

41:43.709 --> 41:45.127
JEON SANG-HO

41:45.211 --> 41:47.963
WEAR AN ACCESS CARD
AND PROTECTIVE GEAR

41:48.047 --> 41:50.174
-Bong-su.
-Oh, is it open?

41:54.720 --> 41:56.138
Where could it be?

41:56.722 --> 41:58.682
Let's quiet down the animals
with some food first.

41:58.766 --> 41:59.767
Okay.

42:01.060 --> 42:05.064
Goodness. All right,
here comes some delicious fruit.

42:05.147 --> 42:07.399
Wait a little.

42:08.984 --> 42:10.903
One for you.

42:11.445 --> 42:14.240
Good. It's all right.

42:14.823 --> 42:16.033
Enjoy.

42:17.701 --> 42:19.245
This won't do.

42:19.954 --> 42:21.330
Hold on.

42:22.164 --> 42:23.958
This is prime Korean beef.

42:25.042 --> 42:27.419
I told your mother
that we needed some meat for the case,

42:27.503 --> 42:29.255
and she packed this.

42:29.338 --> 42:32.258
Geez, I barely get a chance to have it.

42:34.009 --> 42:37.763
The animals have become quiet.
Should we save this for ourselves?

42:37.846 --> 42:39.098
-Should we?
-Let's do that.

42:39.682 --> 42:42.351
You said we had something to find.
What does it look like?

42:42.434 --> 42:45.604
It's a meter-long metal stick
with a hook-shaped end.

42:45.688 --> 42:46.897
Hook?

42:56.949 --> 42:57.950
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

42:59.410 --> 43:00.411
Hello?

43:00.995 --> 43:03.038
-Where are you?
-At the prosecutors' office.

43:03.122 --> 43:06.792
To request a compositional analysis
of Ms. Kim's chamomile tea

43:06.875 --> 43:08.669
and an investigation on Gu Hyo-jung.

43:09.253 --> 43:10.588
I doubt that will work.

43:11.171 --> 43:15.634
Even if a sedative component is found,
that won't be conclusive evidence.

43:15.718 --> 43:18.470
If we aren't careful,
Gu Hyo-jung may catch on.

43:18.554 --> 43:19.930
Then he may run off.

43:20.014 --> 43:23.934
This is more reasonable than relying
solely on Mr. Jeon's memory.

43:24.518 --> 43:26.020
You have a point.

43:26.103 --> 43:30.149
But relying on that unreasonable method,
I found the murder weapon.

43:32.860 --> 43:34.528
You found the murder weapon?

43:35.404 --> 43:36.572
Where?

43:36.655 --> 43:37.740
At the lab.

43:38.449 --> 43:39.575
Are you sure about it?

43:39.658 --> 43:40.659
Yes.

43:41.327 --> 43:42.328
Except that

43:43.287 --> 43:44.997
there's more than one.

43:48.876 --> 43:51.420
But I'm sure it's one of them.

43:52.046 --> 43:54.506
Even if you're right by luck,

43:54.590 --> 43:56.884
it must've been washed
with water or chemicals,

43:57.468 --> 44:00.179
so Gu Hyo-jung's DNA
isn't likely to be found.

44:00.763 --> 44:03.515
Besides, anyone at the lab
has access to it.

44:04.558 --> 44:06.685
It can't be a way to specify him.

44:06.769 --> 44:08.312
You're right.

44:08.854 --> 44:12.024
Speaking of which,
I've come up with a new plan.

44:12.107 --> 44:13.609
I need your help on this.

44:14.568 --> 44:15.736
My help?

44:26.664 --> 44:28.332
ATTORNEY HAN NA-HYUN

44:36.215 --> 44:37.216
Hello?

44:37.299 --> 44:40.427
Hello, this is Attorney Han Na-hyun.
Do you remember me?

44:40.511 --> 44:43.681
Yes, you're Su-jeong's attorney.
How may I help you?

44:44.264 --> 44:47.518
Did you perhaps know
that Mr. Jeon had an attorney?

44:48.102 --> 44:49.812
No, it's news to me.

44:50.896 --> 44:53.065
I sent you a picture just now.
Please take a look at it.

45:05.411 --> 45:07.704
This is Sang-ho's handwriting. What is it?

45:08.288 --> 45:10.749
I visited that attorney's office
a while ago.

45:10.833 --> 45:12.876
It was written on the blackboard.

45:14.211 --> 45:15.212
Really?

45:15.796 --> 45:19.299
And he said something strange.

45:19.383 --> 45:20.717
That the culprit was someone else.

45:22.386 --> 45:25.139
He went outside in a rush after that.
I'm following him right now.

45:25.722 --> 45:27.558
I think he's heading to the lab.

45:27.641 --> 45:29.309
I'll go there now.

45:29.393 --> 45:31.311
I'll get back to you when I'm nearby.

45:33.730 --> 45:35.274
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

45:37.818 --> 45:39.445
Gu Hyo-jung is coming to the lab.

45:40.028 --> 45:41.029
Good job.

45:41.113 --> 45:42.448
What now?

45:44.116 --> 45:45.742
I'll make him confess.

45:46.994 --> 45:47.995
You see,

45:48.745 --> 45:49.997
I'm quite good at that.

45:58.255 --> 45:59.381
A-Are you sure?

46:00.048 --> 46:03.135
Yes, I saw him enter the animal lab.

46:04.261 --> 46:06.597
Actually, there's something
I didn't tell you.

46:07.681 --> 46:09.391
The prosecution is keeping it hush-hush,

46:09.475 --> 46:13.687
but the attorney is
the one who found Mr. Jeon's body.

46:15.189 --> 46:16.231
R-Really?

46:17.649 --> 46:19.359
This may sound weird,

46:20.861 --> 46:23.363
but he's said to be psychic.

46:24.781 --> 46:26.867
Sang-ho's spirit possessed him.

46:26.950 --> 46:29.703
That's how he wrote in his handwriting
and found his body.

46:31.622 --> 46:34.625
Do you still think we're okay on our own?

46:38.962 --> 46:41.840
Sang-ho got killed
and Su-jeong got arrested.

46:42.466 --> 46:45.761
Things are already crazy.
I'd like to handle it myself.

46:51.642 --> 46:53.018
Why are you shaking so much?

46:53.852 --> 46:55.854
Are you scared of ghosts?

46:55.938 --> 46:58.148
Not at all. I'm a scientist.

46:58.232 --> 47:00.108
Ghosts don't exist.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.861
I'll go alone from here.

47:04.404 --> 47:05.906
Why? I'll go with--

47:05.989 --> 47:08.283
No, don't. Well…

47:08.367 --> 47:12.287
It stinks,
and some of the animals are violent.

47:12.371 --> 47:13.372
You better not go inside.

47:14.957 --> 47:15.958
Okay.

47:17.751 --> 47:19.753
RESTRICTED AREA

47:48.532 --> 47:49.783
Hello?

47:50.492 --> 47:51.660
Anyone here?

47:55.163 --> 47:56.164
Hello?

48:01.962 --> 48:04.047
Is anyone here?

48:10.429 --> 48:13.056
You've come, Gu Hyo-jung.

48:14.308 --> 48:16.977
W-Who are you? Are you the attorney?

48:21.440 --> 48:22.858
You haven't come to your senses yet.

48:27.654 --> 48:29.072
Do I still look like

48:30.324 --> 48:31.575
an attorney to you?

48:32.576 --> 48:33.702
If not an attorney, what--

48:37.039 --> 48:38.040
He's coming.

48:39.249 --> 48:40.250
He's coming!

48:40.334 --> 48:41.793
W-Who's coming?

48:46.006 --> 48:48.842
The one you killed. Jeon Sang-ho.

48:50.385 --> 48:52.179
-Sang-ho?
-He asked me

48:52.971 --> 48:54.765
to summon him if he died.

48:55.557 --> 48:56.892
This is ridiculous.

48:57.726 --> 48:58.852
There.

49:00.937 --> 49:01.938
He's come.

49:07.819 --> 49:10.113
That's the formula for the cure.

49:15.160 --> 49:16.161
Why did you do it?

49:25.128 --> 49:27.297
I did nothing wrong to you.

49:28.340 --> 49:29.591
No.

49:29.675 --> 49:31.051
Why did you kill me?

49:31.134 --> 49:33.303
It's a ghost! Help!

49:33.387 --> 49:34.596
A ghost…

49:41.436 --> 49:42.437
ONE HOUR AGO

49:42.521 --> 49:45.023
I'm so nervous. It's my first time
acting as a real-life person.

49:45.107 --> 49:46.400
How do I look?

49:47.943 --> 49:49.903
You kind of look like Sang-ho.

49:49.986 --> 49:51.154
Really? That's good.

49:51.238 --> 49:53.490
What about the voice, though?

49:53.990 --> 49:56.785
This is an AI voice-changing device.

49:56.868 --> 49:58.370
You just have to speak through it.

49:58.453 --> 49:59.496
Oh.

50:01.581 --> 50:02.582
Good.

50:08.839 --> 50:09.840
Listen.

50:09.923 --> 50:13.301
If my acting works,
he'll freak out and try to run off.

50:13.385 --> 50:16.596
And when the flying fake ghost
maximizes his fear,

50:16.680 --> 50:17.889
I'll lead him to confess.

50:17.973 --> 50:20.100
You just have to film it.

50:20.809 --> 50:21.977
Right.

50:23.228 --> 50:25.564
Have you calculated the electricity?

50:25.647 --> 50:27.941
This much overvoltage might cause a fire.

50:28.775 --> 50:30.819
-Bong-su.
-What?

50:30.902 --> 50:33.530
Sang-ho is asking
if you've calculated the electricity.

50:33.613 --> 50:35.824
What matters isn't the calculations.

50:35.907 --> 50:37.701
Movies are all about the feeling.

50:37.784 --> 50:39.369
Geez.

50:41.204 --> 50:42.706
Movies are all about the feeling.

50:53.717 --> 50:54.926
Confess.

50:55.886 --> 50:58.555
Confess that you killed me!

51:03.935 --> 51:04.936
Where are you?

51:08.231 --> 51:09.316
Where are you?

51:11.401 --> 51:12.402
Show yourself!

51:21.036 --> 51:22.287
Where are you?

51:39.054 --> 51:40.806
How could you do that to me?

51:43.350 --> 51:46.019
That time you broke
expensive lab equipment,

51:46.102 --> 51:47.854
I took the blame.

51:48.647 --> 51:49.689
Sang-ho?

51:49.773 --> 51:51.775
I even paid for your mother's surgery.

51:52.984 --> 51:55.195
How could you possibly do that to me?

51:55.278 --> 51:56.571
Is it really you?

51:59.157 --> 52:00.909
I was so good to you.

52:03.370 --> 52:04.412
This makes no sense.

52:04.496 --> 52:05.914
Did you think killing me would do?

52:07.290 --> 52:10.043
That I'd be gone for good, then?

52:10.126 --> 52:12.587
I saw you die before my eyes.

52:12.671 --> 52:15.131
Yes, that's how I died.

52:15.799 --> 52:16.800
But look.

52:18.134 --> 52:19.427
I came back

52:20.262 --> 52:21.596
because I was resentful.

52:22.514 --> 52:24.724
I couldn't rest in peace.

52:28.603 --> 52:29.604
I'm sorry.

52:30.856 --> 52:32.107
I'm sorry, Sang-ho.

52:32.190 --> 52:34.818
Wait. I-I need to record this.

52:34.901 --> 52:35.902
Hold on.

52:37.279 --> 52:39.030
Why isn't it working?

52:47.789 --> 52:50.876
Oh, no! I-rang, there's a fire!

52:50.959 --> 52:51.960
Darn it.

52:56.590 --> 52:57.883
Right, a fire extinguisher.

53:01.469 --> 53:03.972
I'm sorry, Sang-ho. I'm sorry!

53:06.808 --> 53:08.977
I thought it was unfair.

53:09.060 --> 53:12.606
Su-jeong and the Chief depended
only on me until you joined the lab.

53:12.689 --> 53:15.233
I couldn't stand them
turning their back on me.

53:15.317 --> 53:16.943
I didn't mean to kill you from the start.

53:17.027 --> 53:18.361
Liar!

53:19.321 --> 53:20.989
You even prepared the murder weapon.

53:22.949 --> 53:24.326
T-That's…

53:25.994 --> 53:27.495
That, I…

53:27.579 --> 53:30.040
Do you know how dreadful death is?

53:31.166 --> 53:33.585
Do you even know how wretched it is

53:34.586 --> 53:36.212
to leave your beloved family?

53:49.935 --> 53:50.936
What…

54:01.446 --> 54:03.239
What the freak?

54:03.323 --> 54:05.241
It's all fake!

54:08.620 --> 54:10.413
-You fooled me.
-Wait.

54:10.997 --> 54:13.333
Put that down. Let's talk it out.

54:13.416 --> 54:14.417
Talk it out?

54:14.501 --> 54:17.379
Talk what out?
You discovered all that I did!

54:20.799 --> 54:22.300
Just die.

54:22.384 --> 54:23.593
It's for the best.

54:25.136 --> 54:26.346
Attorney Shin!

54:34.270 --> 54:36.314
I told you to wait outside!

54:37.232 --> 54:38.400
Why didn't you listen?

54:39.526 --> 54:40.568
Wait!

54:46.241 --> 54:47.367
No, don't!

55:02.716 --> 55:04.175
Attorney Han!

55:04.259 --> 55:05.260
Thank you!

55:10.849 --> 55:12.308
My name is Shin I-rang.

55:12.851 --> 55:14.477
-Kim Dong-jun.
-Here.

55:14.561 --> 55:17.897
When I was young, kids often teased me
for how my name sounded.

55:17.981 --> 55:19.733
-Shin I-rang.
-Here.

55:19.816 --> 55:21.026
Where is it?

55:21.776 --> 55:22.777
What is?

55:22.861 --> 55:25.321
You like to w-rang-le
with shin-ful ghosts, don't you?

55:25.405 --> 55:26.781
With a ghost!

55:27.657 --> 55:30.660
It didn't bother me much while growing up,

55:31.411 --> 55:34.581
but who knew
I'd actually come to help ghosts?

55:36.916 --> 55:39.711
It's not so bad, though.

55:40.628 --> 55:41.713
No.

55:41.796 --> 55:45.008
I even feel proud when justice prevails.

55:57.937 --> 56:00.148
And there's one thing I newly realized.

56:02.067 --> 56:04.569
Revenge isn't necessarily the reason

56:04.652 --> 56:06.696
why ghosts visit me.

56:45.276 --> 56:46.277
It worked.

56:48.238 --> 56:49.447
It worked.

56:53.118 --> 56:56.788
The cure was developed
thanks to the work of the kind Sang-ho.

57:00.166 --> 57:02.752
-Mom. Can you hear me?
-Honey.

57:02.836 --> 57:05.672
Su-jeong's mother is
slowly getting better.

57:06.506 --> 57:09.425
And her family has regained peace.

57:10.009 --> 57:11.553
Mom, this is U-ju.

57:13.638 --> 57:16.683
Thank you, Sang-ho.

57:18.268 --> 57:19.477
Thanks to you,

57:20.937 --> 57:24.274
we've gained the strength to live on.

57:25.733 --> 57:27.318
I'll do the best I can

57:28.528 --> 57:29.529
to raise our son

57:31.364 --> 57:33.158
so that you won't be worried.

57:34.701 --> 57:35.702
I love you.

57:36.327 --> 57:39.372
I love you, Dad.

57:41.458 --> 57:42.500
Let's go, U-ju.

57:46.379 --> 57:47.505
Hello.

57:48.965 --> 57:50.550
Thank you so much.

57:51.468 --> 57:53.887
You created a miracle.

57:54.471 --> 57:57.348
It wasn't me. You know that.

57:59.142 --> 58:00.143
Yes, I do.

58:01.019 --> 58:02.479
It was my husband, Sang-ho.

58:04.814 --> 58:08.860
But it would've been impossible
without you.

58:10.195 --> 58:11.696
Thank you so much.

58:24.584 --> 58:25.585
Mr. Attorney.

58:27.462 --> 58:28.755
Thank you so much.

58:29.756 --> 58:31.799
I hope you rest in peace.

58:33.510 --> 58:34.511
I will.

59:25.812 --> 59:26.854
As for me,

59:27.855 --> 59:31.568
I've come to realize the great value
of those who keep my side.

59:39.576 --> 59:41.077
He's unharmed.

59:43.037 --> 59:44.372
That's good, then.

59:45.248 --> 59:48.668
My indifferent but caring mom.

59:51.462 --> 59:53.923
-It's good.
-Is it good? I want one too.

59:54.966 --> 59:57.260
-How is it?
-It's good.

59:57.343 --> 59:58.511
Prime Korean beef bulgogi!

59:58.595 --> 01:00:00.263
I-rang is going to love it.

01:00:00.346 --> 01:00:03.266
Thank goodness. Uncle's face
didn't turn red like a monkey's butt.

01:00:03.850 --> 01:00:06.603
And my openly caring family.

01:00:06.686 --> 01:00:08.104
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

01:00:08.187 --> 01:00:09.188
There's one more.

01:00:10.273 --> 01:00:13.610
Attorney Han who chose to believe me
despite how absurd it sounded.

01:00:14.193 --> 01:00:15.194
PARTNER HAN NA-HYUN

01:00:15.278 --> 01:00:17.488
Just what is with Shin I-rang?

01:00:18.531 --> 01:00:19.574
Attorney Han!

01:00:19.657 --> 01:00:20.783
Thank you!

01:00:24.412 --> 01:00:25.413
Whatever.

01:00:26.748 --> 01:00:27.957
I won.

01:00:38.593 --> 01:00:40.595
WON
CLIENT KIM SU-JEONG

01:00:53.107 --> 01:00:56.402
YOUR PACKAGE HAS ARRIVED SAFELY

01:00:57.737 --> 01:01:00.698
Attorney Shin sent the voice recorder
to the guard

01:01:01.324 --> 01:01:03.701
with a note that said
he was sorry for taking it with him.

01:01:05.703 --> 01:01:07.455
Is he kind or just stupid?

01:01:09.374 --> 01:01:10.375
Play it.

01:01:11.167 --> 01:01:14.212
That recording will help me
figure out what he's up to.

01:01:21.678 --> 01:01:23.179
VOICE RECORDING 001

01:01:23.262 --> 01:01:27.350
You follow me from behind
But I race forward

01:01:27.433 --> 01:01:30.895
I run across the table you're seated
I don't care

01:01:30.978 --> 01:01:32.980
If you mess with me, you'll pay the price

01:01:33.064 --> 01:01:34.774
I'm hot, hot, hot, hot, fire

01:01:34.857 --> 01:01:38.569
Before I go wild
Somebody, please stop me

01:01:38.653 --> 01:01:39.696
Stop me

01:01:39.779 --> 01:01:41.823
Stop me, stop me, stop me

01:01:54.127 --> 01:01:56.129
He's a damn nutcase.

01:02:17.108 --> 01:02:19.527
Attorney Shin, are you okay?

01:02:20.027 --> 01:02:21.279
Yes.

01:02:21.821 --> 01:02:24.449
It's probably because I couldn't
sleep much for the past few days.

01:02:24.532 --> 01:02:27.243
You look pale.
I think you should get some rest.

01:02:27.910 --> 01:02:30.705
Okay. I'll go home
after sorting some papers a bit.

01:02:31.247 --> 01:02:33.875
I'm all right. Go home without me.

01:02:34.542 --> 01:02:36.586
-Don't stay too late.
-Okay.

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:50.683
OKCHEON BUILDING

01:02:57.440 --> 01:03:00.109
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

01:03:32.850 --> 01:03:33.851
Again?

01:04:21.941 --> 01:04:22.775
Ghosts aren't coming?

01:04:22.859 --> 01:04:24.777
He's cleaning
for his future living clients.

01:04:24.861 --> 01:04:26.028
He's so excited.

01:04:26.112 --> 01:04:28.281
Hooray for I-rang's independence!

01:04:28.364 --> 01:04:29.866
-Want a case?
-You're the best.

01:04:29.949 --> 01:04:32.785
I'm very experienced
in pre-construction sales cases.

01:04:33.286 --> 01:04:34.453
Attorney Han?

01:04:34.537 --> 01:04:36.205
-Why are you here?
-It's not your business.

01:04:36.289 --> 01:04:37.290
What's with you people?

01:04:37.373 --> 01:04:38.541
It's Seongmyeong Construction,

01:04:38.624 --> 01:04:40.668
a shady company that runs
a pre-sale fraud scheme.

01:04:40.751 --> 01:04:43.004
-A construction gang?
-You're good at fighting, right?

01:04:43.087 --> 01:04:44.797
You little punks!

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:50.845
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
